Scutoscutellar sulci meet transscutal articulation independently. The propodeum is short (twice as wide as long; Fig. 
33C
). Forewing with narrow black bands, absent from costal cell; short, dark setae on dorsal surface of mesoscutum. Hind tibial dorsal setae large and white with fewer large black setae scattered between the white setae. Trochanter and trochantellus whitish yellow on all legs.

(Fig. 
44
) South Africa (Eastern Cape, Northern Cape, and Western Cape provinces).
